<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="O" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Object2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Object,</orth> vb. 1) to propose: <cit><quote>it is well --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.4.43" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 4, 43</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to oppose as an adverse reason or by way of accusation: <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.4.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 4, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.7" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 1, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.1.89" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 1, 89</bibl>. With <cit><quote>against:</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.28" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 28</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.4.116" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 4, 116</bibl>. With <emph>to</emph>: <cit><quote>the saying did not hold in him that did o. the same to thee,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.4.17" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 4, 17</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>